In this example, we define a `NotFound` component that displays a simple message indicating that the user has reached a 404 page. This component can be used as the default route or as a fallback route in a React router configuration. 

To use this component as a fallback route, you can define a `Switch` component and include the `NotFound` component as the last route in the switch:

```
import { Switch, Route } from "react-router-dom";
import Home from "./components/Home";
import About from "./components/About";
import Contact from "./components/Contact";
import NotFound from "./components/NotFound";

function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Switch>
        <Route exact path="/" component={Home} />
        <Route path="/about" component={About} />
        <Route path="/contact" component={Contact} />
        <Route component={NotFound} />
      </Switch>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

In this example, the `NotFound` component will be displayed whenever the user visits a route that does not match any of the other routes defined in the switch.

